cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper discusses model-based learning algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) applications. 
2. cs.LG - The paper proposes new learning algorithms and evaluates them experimentally, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and specifically, reinforcement learning (RL). 
3. cs.RO - The paper discusses the use of RL algorithms in solving Markov Decision Processes (MDPs), which is a common problem in robotics (RO). 
4. cs.SY - The paper discusses the use of real-time dynamic programming (RTDP) to speed up the learning algorithms, which is a common technique in control systems (SY). 
5. cs.DS - The paper discusses the computational demands of the learning algorithms and proposes new algorithms with smaller computational demands, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (DS).
